  "prompt": "How do you restore a Dell Inspiron B130 to the factory settings?",
  "response": "To restore a Dell Inspiron B130 to factory settings, you can try the following methods:\n\n1. Dell Factory Recovery Method:\n- Insert the original Dell Recovery CD/DVD that came with the laptop\n- Restart the computer and boot from the recovery disc\n- Follow the on-screen instructions to restore the system to factory settings\n\n2. Restore Using Dell Recovery Partition:\n- Restart the computer\n- Press F8 repeatedly during startup before Windows loads\n- Select \"Repair Your Computer\"\n- Choose \"Dell Factory Image Restore\" option\n- Follow the on-screen instructions\n\n3. Windows Reset Method:\n- Go to Settings\n- Click \"Update & Security\"\n- Select \"Recovery\"\n- Choose \"Reset this PC\"\n- Select \"Remove everything\" and follow prompts\n\nNote: Since the Dell Inspiron B130 is an older model (released around 2005-2006), these methods might vary depending on the specific version of Windows and installed recovery tools. If possible, consult the original documentation or Dell support for precise instructions for this specific model.\n\nBefore performing a factory reset, always:\n- Back up important data\n- Have your Windows product key ready\n- Ensure the laptop is plugged into power during the process",
